# AI Assistant Context

> This file provides context for AI coding assistants (Claude, Cursor, Copilot, etc.)

## Critical Workflow Rules

**NEVER do these actions without explicit user permission:**
- ❌ `git commit` — Always ask before committing
- ❌ `git push` — Always ask before pushing
- ❌ Creating pull requests — Always ask first
- ❌ Merging branches — Always ask first
- ❌ Deployment commands — Always ask before deploying

**You CAN do without asking:**
- ✅ `git status`, `git diff`, `git log` (read-only git commands)
- ✅ Creating/modifying files
- ✅ Running tests
- ✅ Installing dependencies locally

---

## Project Overview

**ai-talent-network-mcp** is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server providing privacy-first consultant talent search. It is a pilot node for Rakettitiede in a future federated talent network across partner companies.

**Key design principle:** No personal information is stored, processed, or returned — ever. The database contains only anonymized consultant data: new UUIDs (not Agileday IDs), anonymized profile descriptions, skills, project history, and availability. No names, emails, or any other PII.

**Use case:** Searching for consultants by skill or description returns matching "Candidate" entries with skills, availability, and project history — but never a name or identity.

## Architecture

```
Custom GPT / MCP Client
        │
        ▼
ai-talent-network-mcp (Cloud Run)
  ├── MCP tools: search, fetch
  ├── REST API: /api/v1/search, /api/v1/fetch
  ├── OAuth proxy for Custom GPT
  └── SQLite + sqlite-vec (anonymous data only)
        │
        ▼
  GCS bucket (database storage)
```

Data is loaded into the database via an offline import script (not via the server). The server is read-only with respect to data.

## Core Components

- `src/index.mjs` — Express entry point, SSE transport, OAuth, Swagger
- `src/mcp-server.mjs` — MCP tools: search, fetch
- `src/database.mjs` — SQLite search functions (no PII, no external API calls)
- `src/do-search.mjs` — Combines semantic, skill, and project search strategies
- `src/do-fetch.mjs` — Returns anonymized candidate/project details by ID
- `src/results-map.mjs` — Deduplicates and merges results across strategies
- `src/api-router-v1.mjs` — REST API: /search, /fetch
- `src/require-auth.mjs` — API key + OAuth Bearer token auth
- `src/oauth-router.mjs` — OAuth proxy for Custom GPT integration
- `src/embeddings.mjs` — OpenAI text-embedding-3-small (1536 dims)
- `src/storage.mjs` — GCS database download/upload
- `src/constants.mjs` — All env vars and configuration

## Database Schema (anonymous)

- `employees` — id (new UUID), description (anonymized)
- `employee_skills` — skills with proficiency and motivation ratings
- `employee_certificates` — certifications
- `project_history` — past projects (descriptions only, no client names)
- `openings` — availability date ranges
- `employee_availability` — computed view: Available now / Available after DATE
- `vec_employees` / `vec_projects` — vector tables for semantic search

## Search Strategies

Three parallel strategies, deduplicated via ResultsMap:
1. **Semantic profile search** — vector similarity on consultant descriptions (≤0.5 distance, top 10)
2. **Skill search** — tokenized query matched against employee_skills
3. **Project search** — vector similarity on project history descriptions

## Common Commands

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server
npm run dev

# Run tests
npm test

# Check Node version
npm run check-node
```

Requires **Node.js v24.12.0** (enforced by version checker on all scripts).

## Deployment

Tag a version to trigger CI/CD:
```bash
npm version patch -m "fix: description"
git push && git push --tags
```

Never run `git push` via AI assistant — requires YubiKey hardware authentication.

