## Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `API_KEY` | Yes | API authentication key |
| `OPENAI_KEY` | Yes | OpenAI API key for embeddings |
| `GCS_BUCKET` | Production | GCS bucket for database |
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` | OAuth | Google OAuth client ID |
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` | OAuth | Google OAuth client secret |
| `NODE_ENV` | No | development (default) or production |
| `PORT` | No | Server port (default 8080) |

## Testing Architecture

**Fixture-Based Embeddings**: Refresh operations use pre-captured embeddings from fixtures (captured via standalone script). All tests use mock Vertex AI server exclusively - no external API dependencies.

### Test Writing Style

All integration tests must use the **Arrange / Act / Assert** pattern with explicit comments:

```javascript
it('should return candidate when found', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const searchResult = await apiSearch('react');
  const candidateResult = searchResult.results.find(r => r.id.startsWith('candidate:'));

  // Act
  const doc = await apiFetch(candidateResult.id);

  // Assert
  assert.strictEqual(doc.title, 'Candidate found');
  assert.strictEqual(doc.url, RAKETTITIEDE_WEBSITE);
});
```

**Rules:**
- Every `it()` block must have `// Arrange`, `// Act`, `// Assert` comments
- Arrange: set up data, find IDs, prepare inputs
- Act: the single action being tested (one API call)
- Assert: verify the outcome — one logical thing per test
- Skip Arrange if the test has no setup (e.g. pure edge cases with inline inputs)
